{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UaaUozJ2uL6jqxkwRdUpW4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document with all the findings.\n\n## Summary: Scenario.env Format and Fixture Structure\n\nBased on my exploration of the test directories, here's a comprehensive overview of the scenario.env format and fixture structure used in x-agent:\n\n### **scenario.env File Format**\n\nThe `scenario.env` file is a shell-sourced configuration file that defines test parameters. Each file contains key-value pairs that control how a test scenario runs.\n\n**Required Keys:**\n- `SCENARIO_NAME`: Human-readable label for the scenario (e.g., \"gha-agent clean\")\n- `AGENT_SCRIPT`: Path to the agent script, relative to repo root (e.g., \"skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\")\n- `EXPECT_EXIT`: Expected exit code—`0` for pass scenarios, `1` for failure scenarios\n\n**Optional Keys:**\n- `RUN_ARGS`: Arguments passed to the agent script (default: `\"all\"`)\n- `REQUIRED_TOOLS`: Space-separated list of executables required to run the scenario (e.g., \"cargo jq\")\n- Export statements: Custom environment variables needed for the scenario (e.g., `export KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1`)\n\n### **Fixture Directory Structure**\n\n```\ntests/\n  run-scenarios.sh              # Main test runner\n  <agent-name>/\n    clean/                      # Pass scenario (EXPECT_EXIT=0)\n      scenario.env\n      ...fixture files...\n    issues/                     # Fail scenario (EXPECT_EXIT=1)\n      scenario.env\n      ...fixture files...\n    [other variations]/         # Optional scoped or variant tests\n      scenario.env\n      ...fixture files...\n```\n\n### **Real Examples from the Codebase**\n\n**GHA-Agent Clean Fixture:**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/gha-agent/clean/\n├── scenario.env\n└── .github/workflows/ci.yml   (valid workflow file)\n```\nscenario.env content:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"gha-agent clean\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"actionlint\"\n```\n\n**GHA-Agent Issues Fixture:**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/gha-agent/issues/\n├── scenario.env\n└── .github/workflows/bad.yml   (workflow with intentional error)\n```\nscenario.env content:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"gha-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/gha-agent/scripts/gha-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=1\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"actionlint\"\n```\n\n**Kubernetes-Agent Clean Fixture:**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/clean/\n├── scenario.env\n└── deployment.yaml   (valid Kubernetes manifest)\n```\nscenario.env content:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent clean\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\nexport KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1\n```\n\n**Kubernetes-Agent Issues Fixture:**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/issues/\n├── scenario.env\n└── bad-deployment.yaml   (manifest with validation errors)\n```\nscenario.env content:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent issues\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=1\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\nexport KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1\n```\n\n### **Specialized Fixtures: Kube-Agent Variations**\n\n**Scoped Match (tests CHANGED_FILES filtering):**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/scoped-match/\n├── scenario.env\n└── deployment.yaml\n```\nscenario.env:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent scoped-match\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\nexport KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1\nexport CHANGED_FILES=\"deployment.yaml\"\n```\n\n**Scoped No-Match (tests that excluded files are skipped):**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/scoped-no-match/\n├── scenario.env\n└── deployment.yaml\n```\nscenario.env:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent scoped-no-match\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\nexport CHANGED_FILES=\"not-here.yaml other-file.txt\"\n```\n\n**Kubeval Fallback (tests alternative validator):**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/kubeval-clean/\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/kubeval-issues/\n```\nscenario.env:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent kubeval-clean\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"tests/kube-agent/run-with-kubeval.sh\"  # Wrapper script!\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeval\"\nexport KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1\n```\n\nThe wrapper script (`run-with-kubeval.sh`) temporarily hides kubeconform from PATH via shadow directories with symlinks, forcing the agent to fall back to kubeval validation (FR-6 feature requirement).\n\n**Non-Kubernetes YAML Files (tests graceful skip):**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/non-k8s-yaml/\n├── scenario.env\n├── config.yaml        (database config, not a K8s manifest)\n└── settings.yml       (application settings, not a K8s manifest)\n```\nscenario.env:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent non-k8s-yaml\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\n```\n\n**Schema Directory Custom Path:**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kube-agent/schema-dir/\n├── scenario.env\n└── deployment.yaml\n```\nscenario.env:\n```bash\nSCENARIO_NAME=\"kube-agent schema-dir passthrough\"\nAGENT_SCRIPT=\"skills/kube-agent/scripts/kube-agent.sh\"\nRUN_ARGS=\"all\"\nEXPECT_EXIT=0\nREQUIRED_TOOLS=\"kubeconform\"\nexport KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1\nexport KUBE_SCHEMAS_DIR=\"default\"\n```\n\n**No Manifests (tests skip when no files present):**\n```\n/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/kub