{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TMtZvFp4dRbD8s2iCva2ds","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46dcc7a2-447a-40b5-b7b3-893789d3fd2e","uuid":"9567ff7c-d38a-4acf-9ac6-f5e3357baa78","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/exploration.md","oldString":"  - `kube-agent`: validator fallback detection + CHANGED_FILES scoping + skip/fail behavior.","newString":"  - `kube-agent`: validator fallback detection + CHANGED_FILES scoping + skip/fail behavior.\n  - `docker-agent`: Dockerfile discovery (find-based) + hadolint lint + opt-in BuildKit build-check.","originalFile":"# x-agent Exploration Notes\n\n## Key Files & Roles\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/AGENTS.md`: global agent conventions and output contract.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/lib/x-agent-common.sh`: shared Bash helpers for all agents (`step`, `print_result`, `fmt_elapsed`, `setup_outdir`, `setup_lock`, `should_continue`, `need`, `print_overall`).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/run-scenarios.sh`: scenario discovery/execution harness used by all agents.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/01-shared-library-extract.md`: base contract for shared boilerplate.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/02-refactor-existing-agents.md`: how cargo/npm/terra were refactored to source shared lib.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/specs/03-bash-agent.md` through `.ralph/specs/08-docker-agent.md`: per-agent requirements and acceptance criteria.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/docs/agents/scenario-tests.md`: required `scenario.env` contract (`SCENARIO_NAME`, `AGENT_SCRIPT`, `RUN_ARGS`, `EXPECT_EXIT`, `REQUIRED_TOOLS`).\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/docs/agents/definition-of-done.md`: acceptance template for new agent scope.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/docs/agents/add-x-agent.md`: SKILL.md and agent creation pattern.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/install.sh`: skill registry, dependency checks, snippet generation, and library deployment path for `lib/x-agent-common.sh`.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/README.md`: published agent inventory and usage examples.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/skills/*-agent/scripts/*.sh`: reference implementations for shared patterns.\n  - `bash-agent`: minimal runner with syntax/lint workflow.\n  - `gha-agent`: scoped discovery pattern for `CHANGED_FILES`.\n  - `go-agent`: optional build mode + package-scoped execution.\n  - `helm-agent`: multi-command command dispatcher + command-specific failures.\n  - `kube-agent`: validator fallback detection + CHANGED_FILES scoping + skip/fail behavior.\n  - `npm-agent` and `terra-agent`: mature examples of required-tool handling and CI-aware behavior.\n- `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/*-agent/*`: fixture directories for scenario-based validation.\n  - Current pattern includes `clean/` and `issues/` plus scoped fixtures when behavior depends on `CHANGED_FILES`.\n\n## Patterns & Conventions\n- Scripts are Bash 3.2-compatible and start with `set -euo pipefail`.\n- `--help` / `help` / `-h` is handled before dependency or project checks so usage works without workspace context.\n- Required dependencies use `need` and should exit with status 2 when missing.\n- Output contract is strict and step-oriented (`Step`, `Result`, optional `Fix`, `Time`, `Overall`, `Logs`).\n- `CHANGED_FILES` is optional; when set, discovery is narrowed and may become empty (then step-level SKIP expected).\n- `MAX_LINES` is local=40, CI=`999999` unless overridden.\n- Optional tools are surfaced as SKIP with explanatory reason, not hard fail.\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` runs on `skills/*`, `lib/*`, and test scripts before fixture execution.\n- Scenario env values consumed by agents must be exported in `scenario.env` because the harness executes agents as a subprocess.\n- For offline/network-sensitive validation, tests often pin deterministic behavior via explicit env knobs rather than external schema fetches.\n- `KUBE_IGNORE_MISSING_SCHEMAS=1` was introduced for kube-agent to avoid network-coupled validation failures.\n\n## Database Schema\n- No application DB is used by the agent runtime.\n- Control-state and workflow tracking live in `.ralph` metadata files (`ralph-state.json`, logs, and task/plan artifacts).\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n- `tests/run-scenarios.sh` discovers scenarios by scanning `tests/*/scenario.env`.\n- Supports scoped filtering via `CHANGED_FILES` and dependency gating via `REQUIRED_TOOLS`.\n- Exit expectations are numeric (`0` pass, `1` fail, `2` config/tool-missing failure).\n- `shellcheck --severity=warning` failure aborts the scenario run before agent execution.\n- Existing pattern: every scoped discovery behavior should be covered by dedicated fixtures (e.g., no-match/empty-match), especially for file-set filtering.\n\n## Architecture & Data Flow\n- `run-scenarios.sh` enters each fixture directory, sources `scenario.env`, and executes the configured agent script.\n- Agent flow: parse CLI + help/version, initialize common globals, acquire lock (`setup_lock`), create `OUTDIR` (`setup_outdir`), discover candidates, run step functions, and emit step results.\n- Per-step logs are written to files in `OUTDIR`; final output prints `Overall` and `Logs`.\n- External dependencies are only local CLIs (`hadolint`, optional `docker`) and shell utilities (`find`, `grep`, `wc`, etc.).\n- Installer path: `install.sh` must include new skill in `SKILLS`, optional dependency messaging, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet entry.\n\n## Security / Boundaries\n- No network calls are required by docker-agent core flow unless optional `docker build --check` is enabled and docker daemon is used.\n- Command arguments are passed as local CLI/env values; avoid interpolating untrusted strings without quoting to prevent shell globbing/word-splitting issues.\n- Tool execution is local-only; output logs are temporary unless `KEEP_DIR=1` or failure.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":18,"oldLines":6,"newStart":18,"newLines":7,"lines":["   - `go-agent`: optional build mode + package-scoped execution.","   - `helm-agent`: multi-command command dispatcher + command-specific failures.","   - `kube-agent`: validator fallback detection + CHANGED_FILES scoping + skip/fail behavior.","+  - `docker-agent`: Dockerfile discovery (find-based) + hadolint lint + opt-in BuildKit build-check.","   - `npm-agent` and `terra-agent`: mature examples of required-tool handling and CI-aware behavior."," - `/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/tests/*-agent/*`: fixture directories for scenario-based validation.","   - Current pattern includes `clean/` and `issues/` plus scoped fixtures when behavior depends on `CHANGED_FILES`."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
