{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Fs6LZN7uJLVjJpYWvMmoHs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Pq7EwSU3ERaFjt4w8KasWH","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/chrisraethke/projects/x-agent/.ralph/work-summary.txt","content":"# Work Summary — Spec 08: docker-agent\n\n## What was implemented\n\nCreated the complete docker-agent: a lean Dockerfile linter for coding agents.\n\n### Files created:\n- `skills/docker-agent/scripts/docker-agent.sh` — main agent script (~170 LOC domain-specific)\n- `skills/docker-agent/SKILL.md` — Claude Code skill definition with triggers and allowed-tools\n- `tests/docker-agent/clean/` — valid Dockerfile fixture (EXPECT_EXIT=0)\n- `tests/docker-agent/issues/` — bad Dockerfile with hadolint violations (EXPECT_EXIT=1)\n- `tests/docker-agent/scoped-match/` — CHANGED_FILES matching a Dockerfile (EXPECT_EXIT=0)\n- `tests/docker-agent/scoped-no-match/` — CHANGED_FILES with no Dockerfiles (EXPECT_EXIT=0, SKIP)\n- `tests/docker-agent/no-dockerfiles/` — directory with no Dockerfile-like files (EXPECT_EXIT=0, SKIP)\n\n### Files modified:\n- `install.sh` — added docker-agent to SKILLS list, hadolint dependency check, and AGENTS/CLAUDE snippet\n- `README.md` — added docker-agent to agent table, \"Use directly\" section, usage section, and skills list\n\n## Deviations from work plan\n\n- Clean Dockerfile fixtures were simplified (removed `RUN apk add --no-cache curl`) because hadolint DL3018 flags unpinned package versions. Using a minimal `FROM/COPY/CMD` Dockerfile avoids false failures.\n- `setup_lock` was intentionally omitted — consistent with gha-agent pattern (single-tool agents don't need lock contention management). The shared lib's lock is optional.\n\n## Edge cases handled\n- No Dockerfiles discovered: emits `Result: SKIP (no Dockerfiles found)` and exits 0\n- CHANGED_FILES set but no Dockerfile matches: emits `Result: SKIP (no Dockerfiles in CHANGED_FILES)` and exits 0\n- build-check defaults OFF (RUN_BUILD_CHECK=0)\n- docker not installed when build-check requested: emits `Result: SKIP (docker not found)` and exits 0\n- Unknown command: prints usage and exits 2\n- help/--help/-h works without hadolint installed\n- Per-file hadolint execution with aggregate logging (one bad file doesn't hide others)\n- Recursive discovery excludes .git, node_modules, vendor directories\n\n## Tests written/run\n- 5 docker-agent scenarios: all PASS\n- Full suite: 35 scenarios, 0 docker-agent failures (1 pre-existing kube-agent issues failure unrelated to this work)\n- shellcheck --severity=warning passes on all scripts including docker-agent.sh\n\n## Known limitations\n- build-check step cannot be tested in scenarios without a Docker daemon\n- Paths with spaces in CHANGED_FILES are not robustly handled (consistent with other agents)\n- hadolint version differences may produce different rule IDs\n\n## Exploration notes\nUpdated `.ralph/exploration.md`:\n- Added docker-agent to the skills reference list with description of its patterns\n\n## Lessons Applied This Phase\n- Used existing gha-agent as primary pattern reference for single-tool discovery agents\n- Kept clean fixtures minimal to avoid tool-version-dependent lint failures (hadolint DL3018 on unpinned apk packages)\n- Exported CHANGED_FILES in scenario.env (learned from kube-agent iteration — scenario harness runs agents as subprocess)\n\n## Suggestions for the REVIEW agent\n- The kube-agent issues test failure is pre-existing and unrelated to docker-agent changes\n- build-check is intentionally untested in automated scenarios (requires Docker daemon)\n- All 5 docker-agent scenarios pass with hadolint installed\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":244,"cache_read_input_tokens":71894,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":244},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":